<plot>Rita, just back from Brazil, brings a written report to Sandy in Sandy's ground-floor office. While they wait for Tom, a colleague who's late, Sandy notices that Rita looks, well, fuller and firmer. Indeed, Rita tells her that she got plastic surgery in Brazil. She invites Sandy to give her an opinion - do they feel real? As the discussion continues, men arriving at work come to a dead stop outside Sandy's window. Soon after, two men have a water-cooler discussion about a different sort of surgery. Viva la difference.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?401166</url></doc>
